1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a compressed sensing framework for quantitative MRI, which involves image reconstruction and analysis, and can be considered as a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses a random pulse excitation sequence and a random EPI subsampling strategy, which are related to information theory and signal processing. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses an iterative projection algorithm, which can be considered as a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.MS (Mathematical Software) - The paper involves mathematical modeling and simulation of the Bloch equations, which can be considered as a software-related topic. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - This is the least likely category, but the paper involves the analysis of networked systems (i.e., the Bloch equations), which can be related to social and information networks.
